Description: Lightweight Linux maintenance tool for low-spec systems
 fixmylaptop is an interactive command-line tool for everyday Linux system
 maintenance. It checks system health, cleans package caches and temp files,
 shows top resource-heavy processes, and enables performance CPU modes.
 .
 It supports APT, DNF, Pacman, and Zypper package managers, and works on
 most modern Linux distributions without additional dependencies.

 Description: Lightweight Linux maintenance tool for low-spec systems
 fml is designed for older and low-resource Linux machines. It has zero
 dependencies beyond bash and uses no background processes or daemons.